"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-04-paris-2024-olympics-ajayi-ashe-disappoint-in-mens-100m-semis\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Team Nigeria's Kanyinsola Ajayi and Favour Ashe failed to make it to the final of the men's 100m at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games.  The duo were hoping to make a big impression on their maiden appearance at the Olympics.  Ajayi, who came out on top in his heat on Saturday, finished in sixth place with a time of 10.13s in the second semi-final.  South Africa's Akani Simbine won the race in a time of 9.87s, while Letsile Tebogo of Botswana placed second in a time of 9.91s.  Ashe also finished sixth in his semi-final.  The race was won by Jamaica's Oblique Seville in a time of 9.81s, while world champion Noah Lyles finished second in 9.83s.  Kwara United intensify preparation for new NPFL season  Paris 2024 Olympics: I am proud of my girls - Wakama reacts to D'Tigress win over Canada  Championship: Ajayi elated to be back after AFCON injury  Championship: Ajayi returns from injury in Hull City's defeat to Millwall  Championship: Ajayi poised for Hull City comeback after injury layoff  Championship: Ajayi nears Hull City return after injury layoff  Championship: Ajayi set for Hull City return after injury layoff  Hull City manager Jakirovic reveals when injured Super Eagles' Ajayi will play again  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"